{"Title": "Does technology have race?", "Year": 2016, "Source": "Conf Hum Fact Comput Syst Proc", "Volume": "07-12-May-2016", "Issue": null, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 473, "PageEnd": 485, "CitedBy": 24, "DOI": "10.1145/2851581.2892578", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85014734232&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2016 Authors.This paper started as a response to the \"Black Lives Matter\" campaign in the United States, and emerged as a critique of race more generally in technology design. This paper provides case studies of how technologies are often less usable by persons of color, and contextualizes this in light of intersectionalist theory. Finally, it discusses how the HCI community can ameliorate the situation, and our obligation to do so in light of the ACM code of ethics.", "AuthorKeywords": ["Computing", "Race", "Racism", "Social justice"], "IndexKeywords": ["Case-studies", "Code of Ethics", "Computing", "Race", "Racism", "Social justice", "Technology designs"], "DocumentType": "Conference Proceeding", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 0, "EID": "2-s2.0-85014734232", "SubjectAreas": [["Software", "COMP", "1712"], ["Human-Computer Interaction", "COMP", "1709"], ["Computer Graphics and Computer-Aided Design", "COMP", "1704"]], "AuthorData": {"57193539033": {"Name": "Hankerson D.", "AuthorID": "57193539033", "AffiliationID": "60014662", "AffiliationName": "Rainbow Laboratory, Drexel University"}, "56278052500": {"Name": "Marshall A.", "AuthorID": "56278052500", "AffiliationID": "60014662", "AffiliationName": "Rainbow Laboratory, Drexel University"}, "57169810500": {"Name": "Booker J.", "AuthorID": "57169810500", "AffiliationID": "60014662", "AffiliationName": "Rainbow Laboratory, Drexel University"}, "57188723358": {"Name": "El Mimouni H.", "AuthorID": "57188723358", "AffiliationID": "60014662", "AffiliationName": "Rainbow Laboratory, Drexel University"}, "57193532042": {"Name": "Walker I.", "AuthorID": "571935